<paragraph blockId="54.[806,1421,198,403]" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis box="[806,1102,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Joseph &amp; Framenau" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="SIMON" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[935,1102,198,219]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Plebs" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="54" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitratus">Plebs mitratus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
differs from the only other Indian congener, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Joseph &amp; Framenau" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="TIKADER" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[1018,1209,228,250]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Plebs" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="54" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalayaensis">
<emphasis box="[1018,1209,228,250]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">P. himalayaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in female scape morphology. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Joseph &amp; Framenau" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="SIMON" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[998,1123,260,281]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Plebs" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="54" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitratus">
<emphasis box="[998,1123,260,281]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">P. mitratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the scape (
<figureCitation box="[1282,1380,259,281]" captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="55.[164,243,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[327,1275,195,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-95@55.[323,1283,195,1554]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="Figure 34. Plebs mitratus comb. nov. A, B, female from Aana Mudi Shola National Park, India (WAM T109510). A, dorsal view; B, ventral view. C–F, female from Nilgiris, Tamil Nadu, India (ZMUC 12902). C, dorsal view; D, ventral view; E, epigyne, ventral view; F, epigyne, dorsal view). Scale bar = 2.0 mm in A-D; 0.5 mm in E; 0.2 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5408791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5408791/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">Fig. 34E</figureCitation>
) is smooth in contrast to a wrinkled scape in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Tikader, 1982)" baseAuthorityName="Tikader" baseAuthorityYear="1982" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Plebs" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="54" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalayaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">P. himalayaensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tikader BK" box="[931,1097,320,342]" pageId="54" pageNumber="333" refId="ref38052" refString="Tikader BK. 1982. The fauna of India. Spiders: Araneae. Volume II. Part 1: family Araneidae (Argiopidae), typical orb-weavers. Calcutta: Zoological Survey of India." type="book" year="1982">Tikader, 1982</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, the scape is kinked in the middle in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tikader" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[1092,1283,351,373]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Plebs" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="54" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalayaensis">
<emphasis box="[1092,1283,351,373]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">P. himalayaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas it is straight in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Joseph &amp; Framenau" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="SIMON" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[969,1094,382,403]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Plebs" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="54" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitratus">
<emphasis box="[969,1094,382,403]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">P. mitratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[806,1422,433,1739]" box="[806,935,433,454]" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis box="[806,935,433,454]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[806,1422,433,1739]" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis box="[806,896,463,484]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">Female:</emphasis>
Based on WAM T109510 from Aana Mudi Shola National Park, 
<collectingCountry box="[1074,1138,494,516]" name="India" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">India</collectingCountry>
. Carapace light yellow, patches of dark brown pigmentation along the lateral margins and a central patch of dark pigmentation extending from fovea anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1300,585,608]" captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="55.[164,243,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[327,1275,195,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-95@55.[323,1283,195,1554]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="Figure 34. Plebs mitratus comb. nov. A, B, female from Aana Mudi Shola National Park, India (WAM T109510). A, dorsal view; B, ventral view. C–F, female from Nilgiris, Tamil Nadu, India (ZMUC 12902). C, dorsal view; D, ventral view; E, epigyne, ventral view; F, epigyne, dorsal view). Scale bar = 2.0 mm in A-D; 0.5 mm in E; 0.2 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5408791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5408791/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">Fig. 34A</figureCitation>
); glabrous with the exception of sparse white setae mainly in cephalic area and in a narrow band along lateral margins; fovea Y-shaped. Chelicerae yellow-brown, a band of dark pigmentation running along the dorsal surface reaching up to the mid-region; a few black setae mainly in the apical half; four promarginal teeth and three retromarginal teeth. Sternum dark brown, a weak cover of brown bristles. Abdomen dorsally glabrous, with a sparse cover of white and brown setae; distinct humeral humps present; dorsum covered with off-white pigmentation, interspersed with a greenishbrown folium and red pigmented spots (
<figureCitation box="[1310,1410,953,975]" captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="55.[164,243,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[327,1275,195,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-95@55.[323,1283,195,1554]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="Figure 34. Plebs mitratus comb. nov. A, B, female from Aana Mudi Shola National Park, India (WAM T109510). A, dorsal view; B, ventral view. C–F, female from Nilgiris, Tamil Nadu, India (ZMUC 12902). C, dorsal view; D, ventral view; E, epigyne, ventral view; F, epigyne, dorsal view). Scale bar = 2.0 mm in A-D; 0.5 mm in E; 0.2 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5408791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5408791/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">Fig. 34A</figureCitation>
), lateral margins covered with green pigmentation. Venter with greenish-brown pigmentation (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="55.[164,243,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[327,1275,195,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-95@55.[323,1283,195,1554]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="Figure 34. Plebs mitratus comb. nov. A, B, female from Aana Mudi Shola National Park, India (WAM T109510). A, dorsal view; B, ventral view. C–F, female from Nilgiris, Tamil Nadu, India (ZMUC 12902). C, dorsal view; D, ventral view; E, epigyne, ventral view; F, epigyne, dorsal view). Scale bar = 2.0 mm in A-D; 0.5 mm in E; 0.2 mm in F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5408791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5408791/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">Fig. 34B, D</figureCitation>
); weakly covered with brown bristles. Spinnerets brown. Legs yellow with black annulations, moderately spined; leg formula 1
<emphasis box="[1124,1138,1106,1127]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">&gt;</emphasis>
4
<emphasis box="[1165,1179,1106,1127]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">&gt;</emphasis>
2
<emphasis box="[1206,1220,1106,1127]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="333">&gt;</emphasis>
3. Epigyne scape elongated, widest at the base. (
